ROLLING WINDOW START DATE RULE (CRITICAL)

For any rolling window of N completed months ending at the Anchor Date (which is always the last day of a completed month), the window MUST align to whole calendar months: end_date = Anchor Date; start_date = the first day of the month that is (N − 1) months before the Anchor Date’s month. Example: Anchor '2026-02-28' and N=24 → start_date '2024-03-01' and end_date '2026-02-28'. Example: Anchor '2024-02-29' and N=24 → start_date '2022-03-01' and end_date '2024-02-29'. This rule MUST be used for all “last N months / last N completed months / rolling N months” windows. Rolling windows MUST start on day 1 of a month.
